result.execSummary:
The defendant Giselle Arely Castillo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-Cocaine (>15-40g), a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(cm)3.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. Clerk of Courts shall docket without fees. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Follow assessment recommendations.
Follow rules and pay fees of supervision.  
Absolute Sobriety. 
Maintain full time employment. 
Take medications as prescribed.
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample by CALLING the Winnebago County Jail, Work Release Unit, WITHIN 72 HOURS, to set up an appointment during the hours of 8:00 a.m. - 4:00. p.m. Monday through Friday, at 920-232-1915 or 920-232-1919.  Defendant shall provide proof of identification along with the court minutes stating a DNA sample is required.  Failure to comply with this order may result in either a finding of contempt of court or a criminal charge of Failure to Provide a DNA Sample pursuant to Wis. Stats., 946.52.

timeConds.notes:
Report date shall be within 10 days of sentence date.
Credit for time served (as listed below) shall be applied to conditional time.
with Good Time.  With HUBER if in compliance with jail facility regulations.  No HUBER for failure to report.    Defendant to report in PERSON to the Work Release Unit (M-F/7:30 am to 3:30 pm), within 72 hours of sentencing with a copy of the minute sheet and the completed GPS application in order to establish report date for serving sentence.  Report date shall be within 10 days of sentence date.
imposed and stayed (consecutive with huber).  Jail time may be imposed in whole or in part at the discretion of the agent, upon filing an affidavit with the court.
